y bylaws, platform and resolutions and elect national party officers and a judicial committee. Every four years it nominates presidential and vice presidential candidates.<ref>[http://www.lp.org/organization/bylaws.shtml Libertarian Party Bylaws] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080605025750/http://www.lp.org/organization/bylaws.shtml |date=2008-06-05 }}</ref>\n\n==Voting for presidential nomination==\n\n===First ballot===\nAndre Marrou was elected on the first ballot, gathering a majority of the voting delegates, securing nomination.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://mises.org/journals/liberty/Liberty_Magazine_November_1991.pdf | title=My Kind of Town | work=[[Liberty (libertarian magazine)|Liberty]] |via=[[Ludwig Von Mises Institute]] | page=41 | date=November 1991 | accessdate=May 27, 2012 | author=Arthur, Chester Alan | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120801144446/http://mises.org/journals/liberty/Liberty_Magazine_November_1991.pdf | archive-date=2012-08-01 | url-status=dead | df= }}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; text-align:center;\"\n|+ '''1991 Libertarian Party National Convention total vote count: Round 1'''\n|- bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"\n| Candidate\n|bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"| Total votes cast\n|bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"| Percent of votes cast\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"Goldenrod\"\n| '''[[Andre Marrou]]''' ||bgcolor=\"Goldenrod\"| '''257'''|| '''53.32%'''\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"Gold\"\n| [[Richard Boddie]] ||bgcolor=\"Gold\"| 187|| 38.80%\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"Yellow\"\n| [[None of the Above]] ||bgcolor=\"Yellow\"| 20|| 4.15%\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"FFFF66\"\n| [[Hans Schroeder]] ||bgcolor=\"#FFFF66\"| 7|| 1.45%\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFFFCC\"\n| [[David Raaflaub]] ||bgcolor=\"#FFFFCC\"| 6|| 1.24%\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"LightYellow\"\n| Others (scattered) ||bgcolor=\"LightYellow\"| 5|| 1.04%\n|-\n|-bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"\n|\n|colspan=\"5\"|\n{| align=\"left\"\n|'''Color key:'''\n|